============================================================
VARIABLE NAMING CONVENTIONS
============================================================

Prefixes

t = Time domain signal
f = Frequency domain signal

------------------------------------------------------------

Sensors

Acc  = Accelerometer
Gyro = Gyroscope

------------------------------------------------------------

Signal Types

BodyAcc      = Body acceleration
GravityAcc   = Gravity acceleration
BodyAccJerk  = Jerk signal derived from body acceleration
BodyGyro     = Body angular velocity
BodyGyroJerk = Jerk signal derived from body angular velocity

------------------------------------------------------------

Statistics

Mean = Mean value
Std  = Standard deviation

------------------------------------------------------------

Directions

X = X-axis
Y = Y-axis
Z = Z-axis

------------------------------------------------------------

Magnitude

Mag = Magnitude of a three-dimensional signal

============================================================
OUTPUT FILE
============================================================

tidyData.txt

Description:

A tidy dataset containing the average of each selected measurement
variable for each activity and each subject.

Each row corresponds to one subject performing one activity.

